column5: Hi guys and girl I have a job opening for a parts driver at a large and very busy Mississauga dealership. The job would consist off delivering parts ,Keeping wharehouse clean,and helping out where ever else needed. Canidates must be over the age of 25 (due to insurance reasons),able to lift up too 50lbs and have a clean drivers license. Please fax all Resumes to 905 828 1715 attn Dan.
If I can lift 25 pounds twice does that count?? Thanks for giving OFNers first shot at the job, Percher!
Whats the pay like Dan   could always use another job so i can buy more gear lol
I guess I am overqualified and wont get the job because I can lift over 50lbs.  Whats the pay?
